        <heading>Section </heading>
        <content>
          <p>CHAPTER 10.  PRIVATE ADOPTIONS
Art. 1221.  Persons who may petition for adoption
A single person, eighteen years or older, or a married couple jointly may petition to privately adopt a child.  When one joint petitioner dies after the petition has been filed, the adoption proceedings may continue as though the survivor was a single original petitioner.</p>
        </content>
